<font color="#FF0000">..AND THAT'S THE WAY IT WAS..</font><br>
<tt>Mon Feb 23  5:33:27 US/Eastern 1998
</tt><p>
I began posting on this site in November, 1996.<br><br>
This site became a daily part of my life. I am sad about its passing, but rejoice in the lasting true friendships I have made here. <br><br>
Most importantly, I found I was not alone. Emerging from a long self imposed emotional exile with PTSD nipping at my heels, I found I was, and most of all....<br><br>
....a Vietnam Veteran...who was *PROUD* of it!<br><br>
My decorations are now displayed with pride, and I no longer feel as strongly that overriding sense of shame so often felt for all those years. Sure, the old feelings are still there, and they emerge and kick me when I least expect, but I have passed a milestone of sorts on this site, and I feel very good about it! It hurt badly in the beginning with those first few posts. The emotional pain was intense, but as they say...no pain, no gain...how true.<br><br>
All things eventually come to an end, especially those things made by man. Thoughts and feelings, however continue through decades and generations. I hope we have achieved that here.<br><br>
In the words of the famous commentator Walter Cronkite...<br><br>
&quot;... and thats the way it was.&quot;<br><br>
&quot;Th-th-th-that's all folks!&quot; (you know who!) 
<p><code>-- art16@ix.netcom.com  (Arthur Varanelli) </code><p>


